SIMPLE: scoundrel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scoundrel
<hw>Scoun"drel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably from
Prov. E. & Scotch <ets>scunner</ets>, <ets>scouner</ets>, to loathe, to
disgust, akin to AS. <ets>scunian</ets> to shun. See
<er>Shun</er>.]</ety> <def>A mean, worthless fellow; a rascal; a
villain; a man without honor or virtue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go, if your ancient, but ignoble blood⟦br⟧
Has crept through <qex>scoundrels</qex> ever since the flood.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scoundrel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scoundrel
<hw>Scoun"drel</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Low; base; mean;
unprincipled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scoundreldom</ent>⟦br⟧
